children.subject: <md>I would recommend pinning this for visibility by adding #pin to the bottom of the post if you wish!</md>
Anyone interested in finding teammates can join this (unofficial) discord server, which myself and a few others have used this year for coordinating ICPC practices: https://discord.gg/KWPrd6kRH8
Would it be possible to just let students in and then form groups? It's really hard to find teammates for ICPC.
If anyone is interested in teaming up, feel free to email me at asap7772@berkeley.edu!

history.content:
The ACM ICPC Northwest Pacific Regional Contest will be held on Saturday, 5 March. Each team will consist of three members, working on-line and on-site (details to be worked out).  For information on the contest (including eligibility requirements) see http://www.acmicpc-pacnw.org.

This year, I'm trying something new, and asking groups of three to form themselves into teams, and register using the URL https://forms.gle/Me5hGNr87xB8KtJz8.  As the deadline is coming up, you must register this week.

Teams that place high enough can advance to the North American Championship in Orlando during the last week in May.

P. HIlfinger hilfinger@cs.berkeley.edu
